Feature Job Setting Analysis Report
Warehouse Jobs Statistics
The analysis is for the event table: sf_event_table
The analysis period starts at 2022-03-21 23:59:55.799897 and ends at 2022-04-18 23:59:55.799897
The column used for the event timestamp is event_timestamp
The column used for the record creation timestamp for sf_event_table is created_at

STATISTICS ON TIME BETWEEN sf_event_table RECORDS CREATIONS
- Average time is 180.16713693942486 s
- Median time is 180.0 s
- Lowest time is 128.0 s
- Largest time is 541.0 s
based on a total of 3354 unique record creation timestamps.

The BEST ESTIMATE FOR sf_event_table UPDATE FREQUENCY is every 3 minutes

The longer time between record creations are due to 5 MISSING UPDATES.

sf_event_table UPDATE TIME starts 2.004 seconds and ends 55.356 seconds after the start of each 3 minutes

WARNING:
1 JOB is found to have run LATE in relation with other jobs.

The late jobs are:
2022-04-12 12:36:55.355610

WITHOUT THE LATE JOBS, sf_event_table updates ends 5.997 seconds after the start of each 3 minutes

If you believe this won't repeat in the future, you can rerun the analysis by
setting the parameter exclude_late_jobs to True
Job Frequency Recommendation
The RECOMMENDED FEATURE JOB FREQUENCY is 1 minute 1 second after the start of each 3 minutes.
This includes a buffer of 5 s to allow for late jobs.

WARNING:
4 JOBS appear to have recorded late records from missing jobs.
To measure the IMPACT ON THE RECOMMENDATION, the optimal blind spot is computed with and without those jobs.
Those jobs are:

Feature Job Setting Recommendation

In SUMMARY, the recommended FEATUREJOB DEFAULT setting is:

offset: 61
blind_spot: 395

The resulting FEATURE CUTOFF offset is 26 s.

Backtest Result
For the feature job setting:
- Period = 180 s / Offset = 61 s / Blind spot = 395 s
The backtest found that new records would have failed to be processed on time by 1 feature job.
Summary
Key findings:
  • Based on the past records created from 2022-03-21 23:00:00 to 2022-04-18 23:00:00, the table is regularly updated 2.004 seconds after the start of each 3 minutes within a 53.352 seconds interval. At least 4 job failures have been detected.
  • The features computation jobs are recommended to be scheduled after the table updates completion and be set 1 minute 1 second after the start of each 3 minutes.
  • Based on the analysis of the records latency, the blind_spot parameter used to determine the window of the features aggregation is recommended to be set at 395 s.
The recommended Default Feature Job setting is:
  • period: 180 s
  • offset: 61 s
  • blind_spot: 395 s
